The Demise of Net 2805 a rebuttal

By Marge Robbins 1:283/120

It never ceases to amaze me to what lengths people will go to
both  cause  trouble and smear the good names of honest
hardworking Fidonet coordinators of any level.  Mr. Sherwick
does not deserve the abuse he has been taking in this and
related matters.

Let me take a moment to rebutt the accusations contained in
Brent Hamm's article in last week's snooze.

First of all, Mr. Hamm has been excommunicated and that
excommunication has been upheld by both RC14 Steve Sherwick and
ZC1 Bob Satti. That gives him no standing whatsoever in this
matter. Nevertheless he sees fit to attempt to reogranize a net
naming himself as Network Coordinator. Anybody see anything
wrong with this scenario?

BH>Where do you get off disbanding an ENTIRE network without
telling anyone about it?

 When NC Will Wright announced his intention of stepping down
as Network coordinator, the rest of the net was notified by RC14
and given the choice of chosing a new NC or becoming regional
independents. Nobody responded.  Since makenl has a decided
objection to a network without a network coordinator listed, Mr.
Sherwick had no option but to dissolve the network.

BH>Accordingly, we wish to form a new network. We have met all
the BH>requirements of Section 2.4 of Policy 4.07. Here is the
BH>nodelist segment. It's also file attached as NET2805.342.

Two problems with this. An excommunicated node not only doesn't
have a node number, he cannot hold a coordinator position.
Secondly, network coordinators are APPOINTED by the Regional
Coordinator.  Mr. Sherwick has not appointed Brent Hamm or
anyone else to this postion. He asked for a volunteer and got no
response.

The bottom line here is that while the remaining nodes in the
now defunct net 2805 are still members of Fidonet and do have
the option of either reorganizing their net or becoming Regional
Independents, Mr. Hamm has no standing in this matter and his
attempt to reform the net by submitting a bogus nodelist segment
is ludicrous in the extreme.

Marge Robbins
Region 14 Echomail Coordinator
