What We Stand For
Damian Stamm (1:273/406)

The land of freedom. Home of the brave. Land of opportunity.
Liberty, and the pursuit of happiness. All of which we have
been raised.

With the exception of a few. A few who care more about their
own pathetic egos, and less about the actual net.

Our lovely ZC B.S. has decided that he will back inexhonorably
the views of an interim RC. Hence, any comments against the
almighty one will constitute excommunication from the electronic
world of Fidonet.

Guess I'll have to find a new moderator for NBA_ECHO.

What does it say about a person when their whole livelyhood is
based around a computer, where their egos and self confidence
are fueled by the need to be recognized by people who they will
never meet in person in their lifetime? What does it say about
people who make "power" grabs, post as often as they can in Z1*
echoes,  and/or  threaten anything from excommunication to
lawsuits to get people's attention to recognize that they exist?

What matters most to people like B.S. is that people recognize
who he is. That they know he's the ZC, that he's a "president"
of Fidonet. Irrelevant what Fidonet does, what its purpose is
(as a hobby,) but most importantly that he sees his name on his
screen without having to bother to write it himself.

Why is it that B.S. is so scared of criticism that he'll
excommunicate someone as a sign of brotherhood for a fellow Mike
Walsh wannabe?

And how DID B.S. get re-elected in the first place?

There have been many a cry for a new "Policy 5," ditching the
currect virus text that is held so dearly by those in power. In
B.S.'s and their eyes, a legitamate democratic system would be
disasterous, as any questioning of their leadership might end
their possible "power," and they couldn't pull off a Tiennamen
Square excommunication blitz and stay in power.

So until then B.S. will be in power. B.S. and his cronies will
be lined up as RC's and will back him and stroke his ego like
7-year-old with a new puppy.

Now to see how long it takes for my node number to be
revoked........

Damian Stamm
SysOp, Sports And More BBS (1:273/406)
Moderator, NBA_ECHO
